 {"id":"asupersync-1ehla","title":"[SPORK] Registry: Capability-Scoped Naming As Lease Obligations","description":"Implement Spork Registry as a `Cx` capability (no globals).\n\nName ownership is modeled as a lease obligation (reserve/commit/abort) to prevent stale registrations and make naming deterministic + auditable.\n\nGoals:\n- deterministic race resolution\n- cancel-correct registration\n- trace/evidence visibility for ownership changes","acceptance_criteria":"Acceptance:\n- Registry is capability-scoped.\n- Name ownership is two-phase and linear.\n- Lab tests cover race and crash/stale-name scenarios.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-06T02:58:09.251355660Z","created_by":"NavyBeacon","updated_at":"2026-02-08T00:08:05.227555574Z","closed_at":"2026-02-08T00:08:05.227423819Z","external_ref":"bd-3rpp8","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["capabilities","registry","spork"]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1ejpz","title":"HTTP/1.1 parser + serializer","description":"Goal: robust HTTP/1.1 parser/serializer with correct state machine (request/response lines, headers, chunked transfer, trailers, error recovery). Must be cancel-safe and handle partial reads/writes. Include exhaustive unit tests for valid/invalid inputs, header limits, chunked/trailer edge cases, and cancellation-safe behavior.","notes":"Claimed 2026-02-01 by codex-cli (GPT-5). Plan: implement cancel-safe incremental HTTP/1.1 request/response parser + serializer with exhaustive unit tests (valid/invalid, limits, chunked/trailers, partial IO).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"codex","created_at":"2026-01-30T23:34:38.086371418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-01T18:16:12.449233704Z","closed_at":"2026-02-01T18:16:12.449153756Z","close_reason":"Implemented robust HTTP/1.1 parser/serializer: incremental framing with chunk extensions + trailers; TE/CL hardening (reject dup headers/unsupported TE/TE on HTTP/1.0); encode validation; client EOF-delimited bodies; added unit tests. See commits cb72d7f and 26ba09a.","external_ref":"bd-1hiy","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["http","protocol"]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1el2a","title":"[SPORK] Testing: Deterministic Lab Harness + DPOR Exploration For Apps","description":"Make Spork apps first-class lab workloads: seed-sweep, DPOR-style exploration, canonical trace fingerprinting, and invariant oracles.","notes":"Verification pass by TopazIsland (2026-02-08): epic deliverables are implemented and validated; closing to unblock dependent SPORK epics.\\n\\nImplemented surfaces:\\n- Spork app harness + scenario runner: src/lab/spork_harness.rs (SporkAppHarness, SporkScenarioRunner, stable scenario/result schemas, conformance/oracle coverage).\\n- DPOR-style seed exploration + canonical fingerprint grouping + scenario runner fan-out: src/lab/replay.rs (explore_spork_seed_space, explore_scenario_runner_seed_space, summarize_spork_reports, classify_fingerprint_classes).\\n- Public API exports for harness/exploration reports: src/lab/mod.rs.\\n- Crashpack linkage preserved in exploration summaries via CrashpackLink fields in SporkExplorationRunSummary.\\n\\nValidation commands run:\\n- CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/asupersync-topaz-target cargo test --lib explore_spork_seed_space_is_deterministic -- --nocapture\\n- CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/asupersync-topaz-target cargo test --lib scenario_runner_exploration_has_deterministic_fingerprints -- --nocapture\\n- CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/asupersync-topaz-target cargo test --lib summarize_spork_reports_links_failures_to_crashpacks -- --nocapture\\n- CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/asupersync-topaz-target cargo test --lib conformance_single_child_all_oracles_pass -- --nocapture\\n- CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/asupersync-topaz-target cargo test --test lab_harness_report_schema spork_harness_report_schema_is_deterministic -- --nocapture\\n\\nAll above passed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","assignee":"TopazIsland","created_at":"2026-02-06T02:58:23.405967210Z","created_by":"NavyBeacon","updated_at":"2026-02-08T19:32:48.800428944Z","closed_at":"2026-02-08T19:32:48.800361308Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dpor","lab","spork","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1el2a","depends_on_id":"asupersync-rqv3j","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:37Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1emiz","title":"[conformance] Fix TempDir type inference regressions in io tests","description":"Nightly inference now fails on several tempfile::tempdir() match bindings in conformance/src/tests/io.rs, blocking clean rch-backed cargo check/clippy runs on a clean target dir. Add explicit TempDir typing or equivalent direct fix, validate with rch-backed check/clippy/fmt, and keep the change scoped to the conformance IO tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WindyCave","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:04:43.800792317Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T01:52:51.279416401Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T01:52:51.279391956Z","close_reason":"Already fixed in current tree; validated via rch","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":2457,"issue_id":"asupersync-1emiz","author":"WindyCave","text":"Validated current tree and found the reported TempDir inference regression already fixed in conformance/src/tests/io.rs: the three tempfile::tempdir() match bindings now carry explicit tempfile::TempDir annotations at the affected sites. Verification: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check conformance/src/tests/io.rs passed locally; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/rch-windycave-conformance-check cargo check -p asupersync-conformance passed remotely; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/rch-windycave-conformance-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync-conformance --all-targets -- -D warnings also passed remotely. No additional code change was required, so this bead should be treated as already resolved in the current tree.","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:52:47Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1enie","title":"[RANDOM-AUDIT][pipeline] Do not treat SymbolStream::Pending as EOF","description":"In src/raptorq/pipeline.rs poll_next_blocking currently maps Poll::Pending to Ok(None), and receive_object interprets None as stream exhaustion/InsufficientSymbols. This conflates transient not-ready with EOF and can produce false insufficient-symbol failures. Fix with explicit pending error path and add regression test.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GrayGlacier","created_at":"2026-02-22T00:58:07.533657861Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-22T01:08:34.437048449Z","closed_at":"2026-02-22T01:08:34.437023172Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
