 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.18","title":"[audit][blocking-pool] Avoid unchecked idle-timeout subtraction in worker park path","description":"The blocking pool worker loop computes remaining idle park time with a direct idle_timeout minus elapsed subtraction after a preceding branch check. Clippy flags this as unchecked time subtraction, and a saturating or checked subtraction is clearer and more robust against refactors or timing edge cases. Patch the worker park path in src/runtime/blocking_pool.rs to use a non-panicking subtraction and add focused regression coverage if needed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentSpring","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:38:13.600586532Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:43:59.629469523Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:43:58.499840584Z","close_reason":"Completed: blocking_pool now uses saturating idle-timeout subtraction; rch lib clippy passed; rch blocking_pool lib tests passed (35).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blocking-pool","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.18","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:38:13.600586532Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.19","title":"[audit][dns-cache] Make capacity-eviction tie-break deterministic","description":"DnsCache capacity eviction falls back to find_oldest_key() over a HashMap. When multiple entries share the same inserted_at Instant, min_by_key(inserted_at) inherits randomized hash iteration order, so the victim key can vary across runs. Patch src/net/dns/cache.rs to break ties deterministically (preserving oldest-first semantics) and add focused regression coverage for equal-timestamp eviction behavior.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"DarkPrairie","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:40:45.398238664Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:51:21.109218770Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:51:21.109193573Z","close_reason":"Made DNS cache capacity eviction deterministic for equal inserted_at ties; added focused regression coverage; rch cargo check --all-targets and targeted test passed; workspace clippy frontier is unrelated in transport tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cache","determinism","dns"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.19","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:40:45.398238664Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.2","title":"[audit][transport] Clear stale router test imports blocking clippy","description":"Remote clippy via rch currently fails on stale test-only imports in src/transport/router.rs. Remove the dead imports or narrow them correctly, then verify with rch-backed clippy/check on the touched surface so workspace gate progress is less blocked for other beads.","notes":"Router cleanup slice not taken in this session; released due active reservation conflict on src/transport/router.rs and pivoted to asupersync-3qv04.7.2.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"AzureIsland","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:47:10.724009850Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T19:03:44.282476937Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T19:03:41.951356071Z","close_reason":"Already fixed in src/transport/router.rs; test-module imports are live on direct source inspection and no cleanup change is needed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","clippy","quality","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:47:10.724009850Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.20","title":"[audit][server] Make active connection snapshots deterministic","description":"Patch src/server/connection.rs so ConnectionManager::active_connections() does not leak HashMap iteration order. Return active connections in a stable deterministic order keyed by ConnectionId and add focused inline regression coverage for stable snapshot ordering while preserving the existing connection info payload.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SunnyCreek","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-08T22:44:46.216112007Z","created_by":"SunnyCreek","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:52:13.214621939Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:52:13.214598035Z","close_reason":"Completed deterministic active-connection snapshot ordering in src/server/connection.rs by sorting ConnectionManager::active_connections() by ConnectionId and adding focused regressions for deterministic registration-order payloads and strictly ascending connection-id snapshots after removal/reinsertion. Validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 src/server/connection.rs PASS; rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-sunny-conn-tests cargo test -p asupersync --lib active_connections_ -- --nocapture PASS (2 passed); rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-sunny-conn-check cargo check --all-targets PASS. Workspace clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings remains blocked by unrelated redundant_clone lint in active DNS-cache lane src/net/dns/cache.rs:553 and :561.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","server"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.20","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:44:46.216112007Z","created_by":"SunnyCreek"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.21","title":"[audit][types] Make SymbolSet ready_blocks ordering deterministic","description":"Patch src/types/symbol_set.rs so SymbolSet::ready_blocks() does not leak HashMap iteration order. Return ready block IDs in a stable deterministic order and add focused regression coverage.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"TopazLake","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:59:46.961183065Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T23:06:14.619943730Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T23:06:14.619913183Z","close_reason":"Completed deterministic ready_blocks ordering fix and regressions","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","types"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.21","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:59:46.961183065Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2453,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.21","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Patched src/types/symbol_set.rs so SymbolSet::ready_blocks() no longer leaks HashMap iteration order: ready block IDs are now sorted before returning. Added focused regression ready_blocks_are_sorted to lock ascending block-id order across multiple ready blocks. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 cargo test -p asupersync --lib ready_blocks_ -- --nocapture (pass, 2 tests); rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --message-format=short -- -D warnings (pass); rch exec -- rustfmt --check --edition 2024 src/types/symbol_set.rs (pass).","created_at":"2026-03-08T23:06:11Z"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.22","title":"[audit][console] Make Console::with_writer detect the target stream instead of stdout","description":"Console::with_writer currently calls Capabilities::detect_stdout(), so capability detection is based on process stdout rather than the provided writer. That can misclassify non-terminal/test/file sinks as TTY-backed and emit ANSI behavior incorrectly. Fix the detection path to use the target writer's terminal status, keep environment-based color/unicode heuristics, and add deterministic regression coverage for non-terminal writers.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonBarn","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:03:48.786134763Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:23:51.463408108Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:23:51.463383582Z","close_reason":"Validated current tree: Console::with_writer uses target writer terminal detection and focused regression passes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","console"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.22","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:03:48.786134763Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.23","title":"[audit][combinator] Reject empty SelectAll inputs instead of hanging forever","description":"SelectAll::new(Vec::new()) and SelectAllDrain::new(Vec::new()) currently construct futures that can never complete because poll() returns Pending forever for an empty set. Tighten the constructors to reject empty input up front and add deterministic regression coverage so empty selects fail immediately instead of silently hanging tasks or regions.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T01:05:32.303594359Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T01:28:14.874916530Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T01:28:14.874894399Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.23","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:05:32.303594359Z","created_by":"PinkForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","title":"[audit][service] Deduplicate StaticList endpoints to preserve set semantics","description":"StaticList currently replays duplicate endpoints verbatim on first poll and from endpoints(), which violates Discover's set-oriented semantics and can double-insert the same endpoint into downstream balancers/pools. Deduplicate while preserving deterministic first-seen order, add targeted regression coverage, and validate with rch-offloaded cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:06:20.028224339Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:04:08.685485399Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:04:04.453395535Z","close_reason":"Completed: deduplicated StaticList endpoint set semantics with focused regressions and rch-backed check/clippy/test validation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:06:20.028224339Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2456,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","author":"WhiteCliff","text":"Validation update: src/service/discover.rs patch is landed. rch-targeted lib cargo check and clippy passed remotely, rustfmt passed locally, and the earlier tests-check failure was infra-only (worker no-space on /tmp). One focused rch regression test retry was launched but the wrapper never surfaced a final pass/fail line, so I have not overclaimed targeted test success yet.","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:49:59Z"}]}
