+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.28","title":"[audit][service] Make Timeout::with_time_getter honor the custom clock during poll","description":"Timeout::with_time_getter computes a deadline from the supplied clock, but the returned TimeoutFuture::poll path still only consults Sleep and therefore ignores later custom-clock advances unless callers manually use poll_with_time(). Patch src/service/timeout.rs so normal future polling honors the configured time_getter while still registering a wake source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CopperLake","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:24:00.024731249Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T01:24:00.024731249Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service","timeout"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.28","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:24:00.024731249Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.29","title":"[audit][runtime] Make deadline monitor no-progress warnings logical-time aware after checkpoints","description":"Fresh-eyes audit slice: DeadlineMonitor only falls back to logical time before the first checkpoint, so a task that checkpointed once can evade NoProgress warnings in lab-style runs where logical time advances while wall time stays mostly stable. Fix the monitor to track logical progress after observed checkpoints and add a focused regression test.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PearlPeak","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:26:01.020710136Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T01:31:47.912156914Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T01:31:47.912138129Z","close_reason":"Completed: logical-time no-progress warnings now work after checkpoints; added focused regression and validated with rch","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.29","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:26:01.020710136Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.3","title":"[audit][time] Clamp overdue timer_driver next_deadline to now","description":"TimerDriver::next_deadline() currently forwards the wheel's stale internal deadline even after the underlying clock has already advanced past it. That leaks an overdue absolute deadline to callers instead of reporting the timer as immediately due. Fix next_deadline to compare against the current clock time and clamp overdue deadlines to now, preserving None for no timers and the real future deadline otherwise. Add deterministic regression tests for both TimerDriver and TimerDriverHandle.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GoldBasin","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:49:01.453506616Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T01:58:07.151259356Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T01:58:07.143029768Z","close_reason":"Completed; src/time/driver.rs implementation landed, rch cargo check --lib passed, repo-wide cargo test/check/clippy remain blocked by unrelated kafka test imports, service/buffer clippy findings, and existing fmt drift in other lanes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","time","timers"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:49:01.453506616Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
