+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.31","title":"[audit][service] Defuse load metric if load-balanced dispatch panics","description":"LoadBalancer::call_balanced() increments the chosen backend's in-flight metric before invoking service.call(req). If the backend panics synchronously while constructing its future, the increment is leaked and that backend remains permanently overloaded. Add a small guard in src/service/load_balance.rs so synchronous panics unwind cleanly without leaking load, rename any underscore-bound fields needed to satisfy clippy, and add a focused regression that catches a panic from call_balanced() and verifies loads() returns to zero.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PearlPeak","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T01:51:04.056069202Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:26.965960957Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:26.965935059Z","close_reason":"Completed by PinkForest: load-balance panic guard landed and was validated via targeted rch check/clippy/test runs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.31","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:51:04.056069202Z","created_by":"PinkForest"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.32","title":"[audit][service] Restore reserved rate-limit token if inner.call panics","description":"RateLimit consumes a token in poll_ready() before dispatch, but call() forwards directly to inner.call(req). If the inner service panics synchronously while constructing its future, the reserved token is leaked until refill even though no request was actually dispatched. Patch src/service/rate_limit.rs to restore the reserved token on unwind, add focused regression coverage that catches the panic and verifies available_tokens() is unchanged, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PearlPeak","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T01:54:35.022523359Z","created_by":"PearlPeak","updated_at":"2026-03-09T01:57:30.965217017Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.32","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:54:35.022523359Z","created_by":"PearlPeak"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","title":"[audit][test] Decouple Trace capture from implicit stderr printing in TestLogger","description":"TestLogger::new(TestLogLevel::Trace) currently flips verbose=true, so asking for maximal event capture also causes immediate stderr emission from library test-support code. Make verbosity explicit instead of coupling it to Trace, add regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925143002Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925119328Z","close_reason":"Completed: TestLogger trace capture no longer implies verbose stderr output; file-local rustfmt and UBS clean, rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed, focused rch test passed, clippy remains blocked only by unrelated src/channel/oneshot.rs lint frontier","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","title":"[audit][evidence] Make evidence_sink timestamps deterministic","description":"src/evidence_sink.rs currently stamps emitted EvidenceLedger entries with SystemTime::now() in non-test helper functions, which makes scheduler/cancel/budget evidence nondeterministic and bypasses the runtime's explicit time capability. Replace the ambient wall-clock stamping with a deterministic timestamp source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaHollow","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:03:28.921765757Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:27:04.869450201Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:27:04.869422099Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","evidence"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:03:28.921765757Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2458,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Validation currently blocked by shared compile frontier in src/service/reconnect.rs (lifetime error at line 271 during rch-backed evidence_sink test run); patch in src/evidence_sink.rs is formatted and awaiting rerun once lib compiles again.","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:47Z"},{"id":2459,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Implemented deterministic sink-owned evidence timestamps in src/evidence_sink.rs: added EvidenceSink::next_evidence_ts(), backed JsonlSink and CollectorSink with AtomicU64 sequences, switched scheduler/cancel/budget emit helpers off SystemTime::now(), and added regression test emit_helpers_use_deterministic_timestamp_sequence. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/evidence_sink.rs ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO