+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.35","title":"[audit][service] Make Oneshot transition safely if inner call panics","description":"ServiceExt::oneshot takes the request out of its Ready state before invoking service.call(req). If that synchronous call panics while constructing the inner future, a caught unwind leaves the Oneshot future stuck in Ready with request=None instead of moving to a terminal state. Patch src/service/service.rs so the panic path leaves Oneshot internally consistent, add a focused regression that catches the first panic and verifies the future is no longer poisoned with the wrong invariant, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CyanDesert","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:08.146146717Z","created_by":"CyanDesert","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:18:12.319860801Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:18:12.319834712Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.35","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:08.146146717Z","created_by":"CyanDesert"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.36","title":"[audit][runtime] Finish uninterruptible JoinFuture migration in task_handle","description":"Current worktree changes partially switch TaskHandle::join()/join_with_drop_reason() to recv_uninterruptible(), but the shared lib frontier still reports JoinFuture construction type mismatches in src/runtime/task_handle.rs. Finish the migration coherently, keep drop/cancel semantics intact, add focused regression coverage if behavior changes, and validate with rch-backed targeted commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:15.451211487Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:11:08.855625200Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:11:08.855600714Z","close_reason":"Already fixed in current tree by concurrent join migration; validated via rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","compile","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.36","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:15.451211487Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.37","title":"[audit][service] Mark refresh_pending when Reconnect::call panics","description":"Reconnect::call currently invokes inner.call(req) directly and only the returned ReconnectFuture can set refresh_pending. If inner.call(req) panics synchronously while constructing the future, no ReconnectFuture exists, so refresh_pending stays false and the wrapper can keep reusing the same broken inner service on the next poll_ready. Add an unwind guard that marks refresh_pending on synchronous panic, add a focused regression, and validate with rch-backed check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:11:41.778678308Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:27.006584161Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:26.998357304Z","close_reason":"Completed: reconnect now marks refresh_pending on synchronous inner.call panic, with focused regression and targeted rch validation.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.37","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:11:41.778678308Z","created_by":"PinkForest"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","title":"[audit][rate_limit] Restore consumed rate-limit token if guarded operation or web handler panics","description":"Both the core combinator and the sync web adapter consume a rate-limit token before invoking user code. In src/combinator/rate_limit.rs, RateLimiter::call_weighted() acquires tokens and then runs op() without an unwind guard, so a synchronous panic burns tokens even though the operation never completed. In src/web/middleware.rs, RateLimitMiddleware::call() uses limiter.try_acquire() and then calls the inner handler directly, so a panicking handler leaks the consumed token in the same way. Add a narrow refund path for panic unwind, route the web middleware through the panic-safe helper, add focused regression coverage in both modules, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362203392Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362173717Z","close_reason":"Refund consumed rate-limit tokens on synchronous panic in combinator and web middleware; focused rch regressions passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","combinator","rate-limit","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","title":"[audit][grpc] Make tracing interceptor request IDs deterministic","description":"src/grpc/interceptor.rs currently generates x-request-id values from SystemTime::now(), which makes request IDs nondeterministic and introduces ambient wall-clock authority into library code. Replace that clock-based ID generation with a deterministic interceptor-owned source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaHollow","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909958605Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909932226Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2460,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Replaced TracingInterceptor request ID generation in src/grpc/interceptor.rs with a deterministic interceptor-owned AtomicU64 counter shared across clones, preserving caller-supplied x-request-id values and removing ambient SystemTime usage. Added focused regressions tracing_interceptor_uses_deterministic_sequential_ids and tracing_interceptor_preserves_existing_request_id. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/grpc/interceptor.rs ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/