 {"id":"asupersync-3qv04.8","title":"[WASM] Quality spine: unit coverage, E2E harnesses, and failure forensics","description":"Make test coverage, end-to-end verification, and failure forensics explicit first-class work rather than assuming they will emerge organically from implementation. This track exists because a usable JS/TS/WASM library needs more than green builds: it needs proofs that package entrypoints, ABI handles, browser host bridges, React/Next adapters, and unsupported-environment behavior all work under deterministic automated tests with logs rich enough to debug real failures quickly.\n\nThis track is intentionally cross-cutting. It captures the unit/integration/E2E pyramid, the harness scripts that exercise packaged artifacts, the logging/retention rules for browser failures, and the CI entrypoints that make the evidence reproducible for future agents and humans.","status":"in_progress","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":1440,"created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:43.008592599Z","created_by":"CopperForest","updated_at":"2026-03-08T18:40:55.561079302Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","qa","testing","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:43.008592599Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.1","title":"[WASM][QA] Define required evidence matrix for unit, integration, E2E, and logging coverage","description":"Define the test-evidence contract for Browser Edition before implementation sprawls further. Enumerate what every layer must prove: Rust cfg/feature gating, exported ABI handle safety, JS/TS type surface behavior, browser host-bridge correctness, React/Next adapter lifecycle behavior, bundled-package installability, and cross-browser execution.\n\nAlso define the logging and artifact-retention rules so failures are diagnosable: console capture, browser logs, network traces where relevant, screenshot/video policy, wasm/module version identifiers, package versions, and exact repro commands. This bead is the quality-plan anchor that keeps later implementation beads from calling themselves done with only ad hoc testing.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:45.825464641Z","created_by":"CopperForest","updated_at":"2026-03-06T18:40:36.869454843Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T18:40:36.869431339Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["design","qa","testing","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:45.825464641Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2409,"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.1","author":"CopperForest","text":"Reopened during the second audit. The bead description usefully defines the intended evidence matrix, but that planning text is not the same thing as having an implemented artifact/contract in the repo, so this work remains open until that concrete surface exists.","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:34:00Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","title":"[WASM][QA] Add Rust unit and integration coverage for cfg gates, ABI handles, and browser contracts","description":"Organize the Rust-side automated proof surface for Browser Edition as a three-part quality lane: cfg/native-leak compile invariants, exported-handle ownership/outcome/cancellation invariants, and browser-contract semantic coverage close to the runtime core.\n\nThis is now an umbrella QA epic rather than a single undifferentiated task. Its child beads make the proof surface explicit enough that implementation can proceed without hand-wavy claims that Rust-side testing will somehow be comprehensive.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","assignee":"TurquoiseDune","estimated_minutes":360,"created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:48.565483905Z","created_by":"CopperForest","updated_at":"2026-03-07T21:32:45.648153759Z","closed_at":"2026-03-07T21:32:45.648129534Z","close_reason":"Closure audit complete: all child Rust QA beads closed with in-repo evidence for cfg compile invariants, ABI handle lifecycle, and browser contract coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["qa","rust","tests","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:16:17.741652620Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:16:20.358009259Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:16:22.946235883Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:13:48.565483905Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2437,"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.8.2","author":"TurquoiseDune","text":"Closure audit by TurquoiseDune: child beads 3qv04.8.2.1/8.2.2/8.2.3 are all closed; evidence surfaces are present in-tree and mapped to the three QA lanes. Verified cfg/profile compile harness file tests/wasm_cfg_compile_invariants.rs (matrix + backstop ignored tests), ABI boundary coverage in tests/wasm_abi_compatibility_harness.rs and tests/wasm_abi_handle_lifecycle_contract.rs, and browser-contract Rust coverage in src/io/browser_stream.rs + src/io/browser_storage.rs + src/types/wasm_abi.rs with dense unit-test blocks. This epic can be closed as complete and unblocks downstream 3qv04.8.6 from the Rust-coverage side.","created_at":"2026-03-07T21:31:54Z"}]}
